    "what_description": "Withania somnifera is a perennial plant with a woody root and erect or prostrate stems, reaching 1-3 meters in height, and 10-20 cm in diameter. It belongs to the family Solanaceae. The leaves are simple, alternate, elliptical or ovate, 8-15 cm long, and 4-10 cm wide, with a cuneate base and an acuminate apex, and are glabrous or tomentose on the lower surface. The inflorescence is a corymb, with small, yellowish flowers, 4-6 mm in diameter, and 6-8 mm long. The fruit is a berry, 6-8 mm long and 4-6 mm in diameter, with 2-4 seeds per berry.",
