    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Withania somnifera are rooted in its ability to protect against oxidative stress through its antioxidant properties, attributed to the presence of flavonoids and polyphenols. Withania somnifera has been found to exhibit anti-inflammatory effects, which are partly due to the saponin content of the plant, helping to mitigate the severity of inflammatory conditions. Furthermore, this plant has been shown to possess neuroprotective properties, thanks to the bioactive compounds like withanolides and sitoindosides, which have been found to exert neurotrophic effects and promote neuronal survival. Additionally, the antimicrobial properties of Withania somnifera have been linked to the presence of volatile oils and triterpenoids, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms. By modulating the immune system, Withania somnifera's immunomodulatory properties help to regulate the body's response to pathogens and prevent the onset of autoimmune diseases.",
