    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Withania somnifera are withanolides, which include withaferin A, withanone, and withanolide A, that are responsible for its anti-inflammatory, anti-oxidant, and anti-cancer properties. Withanolide A has been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, while withanone has been found to scavenge free radicals and reduce oxidative stress. Withanoside IV has been reported to have immunomodulatory effects by enhancing the activity of natural killer cells and increasing the production of antibodies. Withanolides also exhibit anti-proliferative and pro-apoptotic activities, making them effective against cancer cells. The collective action of these constituents contributes to the herb's adaptogenic, anti-stress, and anti-ageing properties, making it a valuable natural remedy for various health conditions.",
