    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Withania somnifera are derived from its roots and include ashwagandha tea, made by infusing dried roots in hot water, which is traditionally used to reduce stress and anxiety due to its alkaloids and saponins content. Ashwagandha capsules contain a standardized extract of the root, offering a concentrated form of the herb, which has been shown to improve sleep quality and cognitive function in several human studies. Ashwagandha tincture is a liquid extract of the root, commonly used in Ayurvedic medicine to enhance adaptogenic properties and promote relaxation. Ashwagandha oil is a topical preparation used for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, which may help soothe skin irritations and reduce stress-related symptoms. Ashwagandha powder is a dried and powdered root extract, often used as a dietary supplement to support immune function and reduce oxidative stress.",
