    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effect of using Withania somnifera are numerous and can be attributed to its bioactive compounds which interact with other medications. Using Withania somnifera improperly may lead to interactions with blood thinners such as warfarin due to its anticoagulant properties. Additionally, improper use can cause liver damage due to the presence of withanolides which have been shown to induce liver toxicity in high doses. Furthermore, consuming excessive amounts of Withania somnifera may cause gastrointestinal disturbances including diarrhea, nausea, and vomiting. Moreover, Withania somnifera may also raise blood pressure in individuals with pre-existing hypertension, exacerbating cardiovascular conditions."
